the patient suffers adverse reactions to the treatment regimen 32
or the treatment regimen fails. 33
Sec. 4741.041. (A) As used in this section : 34
(1) "Human food product" means livestock raised for human 35
consumption or livestock whose products are used for human 36
consumption. 37
(2) "Livestock" means porcine animals, bovine animals, 38
caprine animals, ovine animals, and poultry. 39
(3) "Tele-advice" means the provision of any health 40
information, opinion, or guidance by a veterinary professional 41
that is not intended to diagnose, treat, issue certificates of 42
veterinary inspection, or issue prognoses of the physical or 43
behavioral illness or injury of an animal or issue. A 44
