(B) A licensed veterinarian may conduct the practice of 48
veterinary medicine via telehealth services if all of the 49
following apply: 50
(1) The veterinarian obtains the informed consent from the 51
client, including an acknowledgement that the standards of care 52
prescribed by this chapter equally apply to in-person and 53
telehealth visits. The veterinarian shall maintain documentation 54
of the consent for at least three years after receiving the 55
informed consent. 56
(2) The veterinarian provides the client with the 57
veterinarian's name and contact information and secures an 58
alternate means of contacting the client if the telehealth visit 59
is interrupted. Following the telehealth visit, the veterinarian 60
shall make available to the client an electronic or written 61
record of the visit. The electronic or written record shall 62
include the veterinarian's license number. 63
(3) Before conducting an evaluation of a patient via a 64
telehealth visit, the veterinarian advises the client of all of 65
the following: 66
(a) The veterinarian may ultimately recommend an in-person 67
visit with the veterinarian or another licensed veterinarian; 68
(b) The veterinarian is prohibited under federal law from 69
prescribing certain drugs or medications based only on a 70
telehealth visit; 71
(c) The appointment for a telehealth visit may be 72
terminated at any time. 73

