(D)(1) Except as provided in division (D)(2) of this 91
section, a licensed veterinarian whose client is engaged in the 92
raising of livestock for human food products may not use 93
telehealth services for those livestock unless the veterinarian 94
has established a veterinary-client-patient relationship in 95
person with respect to those livestock prior to the use of 96
telehealth services. 97
(2) A licensed veterinarian whose client is engaged in the 98
raising of livestock for human food products may conduct tele- 99
advice services for those livestock prior to the veterinarian 100
establishing a veterinary-client-patient relationship in person 101
with the client. 102

